emacspeak (31.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release.
  * Incorporated various improvements collected during several years of
    extensive use.
  * Separate package for html documentation.
  * Excluded plain text, pdf and ps documentation formats.
  * Build shared libraries for Outloud and eSpeak speech servers.
  * Provide Outloud and eSpeak speech servers in separate architecture
    dependent packages.
  * Cleared out the tcl field in blurbs since Emacspeak doesn't care
    about DTK_TCL variable anymore.
  * Modified emacspeakconfig script to fit better for serving software
    TTS based speech servers and to produce correct configuration file
    according to actual sense of DTK_TCL and DTK_PROGRAM environment
    variables.
  * Dropped alternatives for /usr/bin/emacspeak.
  * Removed dtk-soft speech server because it cannot be properly
    compiled without proprietary software.
  * Don't copy blurbs into the flavor related tree, so compatibility
    with emacspeak-ss is dropped, but eflite should survive.
  * Moved tcl and tclx from dependencies to recommendations since these
    means are not essential for Emacspeak itself, but only for speech
    servers that are not mandatory and can be replaced by Multispeech or
    Eflite that do not require tcl.
  * Don't take care of Emacs load-path list in startup file since
    Emacspeak does it properly itself.
  * Remove unused variable emacspeak-info-directory. Anyway, the
    directory it points to does not exist in this installation.
  * When starting Emacspeak, environment variables EDITOR and VISUAL are
    set to use emacsclient as the default editor if possible. It will
    affect shell commands started from within Emacs.

 -- Igor B. Poretsky <poretsky@mlbox.ru>  Sat, 06 Feb 2010 03:52:33 +0300

